data.chText: 在…上写（词语、名字等）；题；刻
data.enText: to write or cut words, your name, etc. onto sth
His name was inscribed on the trophy.
The trophy was inscribed with his name.

data.chText: 她在书上签了名，并题词“谨致深切的感谢”。
data.enText: She signed the book and inscribed the words ‘with grateful thanks’ on it.

simple_means.memory_skill: in 进入 + scrib 写 + e → 写进去 → 铭刻

tr: address, (a work of literature) in a style less formal than a dedication

example: We should encode the message for security reasons

tr: write, engrave, or print as a lasting record
carve, cut, or etch into a material or surface
example: engraved the trophy cupt with the winner's
the lovers scratched their names into the bark of the tree

tr: draw within a figure so as to touch in as many places as possible
register formally as a participant or member
example: The party recruited many new members

value.def: If you inscribe words on an object, you write or carve the words on the object.

example.ex: Some galleries commemorate donors by inscribing their names on the walls...
example.tran: 一些美术馆把捐赠者的姓名镌刻在墙上以示纪念。

example.ex: She and Mark read the words inscribed on the inner walls of the monument.
example.tran: 她和马克读了刻在纪念碑内墙上的文字。

example.ex: ...a silver cigarette-case, inscribed 'To Laura, with all my love, Leonard'.
example.tran: 刻有“献给劳拉,深爱你的伦纳德”字样的一个银质烟盒

value.def: If you inscribe something in the front of a book or on a photograph, you write it there, often before giving it to someone.

example.ex: On the back I had inscribed the words: 'Here's to Great Ideas! John'...
example.tran: 在背后我题写了这样的话：“愿奇思妙想不绝！约翰”。

example.ex: The book is inscribed: To John Arlott from Laurie Lee.
example.tran: 书的题赠是：献给约翰·阿洛特——劳丽·李。

partsOfSpeech.dec: a 加强 + scrib 写 + e → 把账记在…头上 → 归因于
a 加强 + scrib 写 + able 可…的 → 可归因于…的
circum 环绕 + scrib 写 + e → 画一个圈 → 立界限；限定
con 共同 + scrib 写 + e → 大家写上〔名字〕→ 征募
de 加强 + scrib 写 + e → 着重写 → 描写
de 加强 + script 写 + ion 表动作 → 描绘
in 进入 + scrib 写 + e → 写进去 → 铭刻
in 进入 + script 写 + ion 表物 → 铭刻；碑文
manu 手 + script 写 → 手抄本；原稿
post 后 + script 写 → 写在后面〔的文字〕→ 附言
pre 预先 + scrib 写 + e → 预先写好要求 → 指示
pre 预先 + script 写 → 预先写下的东西 → 命令，法令
pre 前；预先 + script 写 + ion，prescript 的名词 → 处方；命令
scribb〔= scrib〕写 + le 表反复，连续 → 乱写
scrib 写 + e → 书法家
script 写 + ure 行为有关的物 → 写出的〔宗教作品〕原本 → 圣经
sub 下 + scrib 写 + e → 在单子下面写上名字 → 订阅；认购
subscrib〔e〕订阅；认购 + er 表名词 → 订户；捐助人
trans 转移 + scrib 写 + e → 写到别的地方 → 抄写
trans 转移 + script 写 → 副本，抄本
